column3: â€œTested about 18% cbd less than 1% thc. Aroma was amazingly appealing of sweet skunky pine. Buds were somewhat loose and leafy compared to what i'm used to, but harvesting a little prematurely is a technique growers use to maximize cbd ratios. I don't have any serious pathology so cannot comment on the effects against  pain, spasms so forth. To me the high" was more of an equalizing and calming of the psyche
â€œmy favorite CBD strain. I got an 18:1 ratio (CBD:THC) and it's perfect for taming my anxiety while still keeping me awake, and for helping me focus.â€

â€œSince itâ€™s a CBD strain and not THC heavy, the effects are minimal. More in line with cold medicine, but the most notable aspect is a nice mood elevation. â€œHad foot surgery, super painful, did not like oxycodone so tried this. Amazing pain relief with no high, just a relaxed calm sense of well being.â€

â€œVery good strain. Has more of a honey/sweet and flowery smell and taste I found. Very mellow and smooth. While it has a little bit too much THC for my likings, I enjoyed the high. Unexpectedly sleepy, but mostly very relaxed, while also being a clear headed buzz.â€

â€œA pleasant, pain-relieving strain with a very high CBD to THC ratio. I get the most out of this one when combined with a little of a happy" sativa (daytime) or a sleepy indica (evening). Ironically for a pain-relieving strain
